### Base URL
@baseUrl = https://todu.mn/bs/lms/v1
@token = cSIzGj2fVXyq2dsG9CktqQ
@userId = 539

### Login with email & password
POST {{baseUrl}}/token/email
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "schoolstudent@must.edu.mn",
  "password": "123",
  "push_token": ""
}


###
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Alternative: Get enrolled courses explicitly
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/courses/enrolled
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. Group APIs – Student Access
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Set a course ID (replace with actual from step 2)
@courseId = 204

### 3.1 Get all groups of a specific course
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/{{courseId}}/groups
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 3.2 Get details of a specific group (use groupId from response above)
@groupId = 204
GET {{baseUrl}}/groups/{{groupId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3.3 Get all users enrolled in a course (shows which group each user belongs to)
### Note: Some endpoints may be restricted to teachers; try if student has access.
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/{{courseId}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
?current_user=

### 3.4 Get current user's specific enrollment info in a course (includes group_id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/{{courseId}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
# Note: The spec does not have /users/me under course, but you can use /courses/{courseId}/users/{userId}
# with userId from /users/me. Example below:

### Get current user's ID first
@myUserId = 789
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/{{courseId}}/users/{{myUserId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}